import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    values = data['values']
    plt.hist(values, bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the distribution of values in the volcano dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['width'], data['height'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xlabel('Width')
    plt.ylabel('Height')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between the width and height of the volcano?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.gca()
    ax.boxplot(data['values'])
    ax.set_xticklabels(['Values'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    avg_value = data['values'].mean()
    ax.axhline(avg_value, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Value: {avg_value:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    
    plt.title('What is the average value of the volcano?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
